{"title":"Trek updates Boone CX Bike with aero tubes, lighter frame & fully internal cable routing","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/10/trek-2022-boone-gets-aero-treatment-t47-bottom-bracket-and-internal-cable-routing/","date":1631281843000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091444/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-full-bike--800x600.jpeg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"Trek Boone 2022 Red full bike\" loading=\"eager\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-271102\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>There is a steady stream of exciting bike news coming, and with the UCI ‘cross season just a week away, Trek let the new Boone out of the bag. Since its inception, the Trek Boone amassed many victories, including National Champions (for many Nations) World Cup wins and reaching a pinnacle last year — a World Championship piloted by Baloise-Treks, Lucinda Brand.</p><div id=\"attachment_271123\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone-.jpeg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271123\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone-.jpeg\" alt=\"Brand Victory Trek Boone\" width=\"1280\" height=\"640\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone--297x149.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone--800x400.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone--120x60.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone--768x384.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone--297x149.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone--800x400.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone--120x60.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10092219/Brand-Victory-Trek-Boone--768x384.jpeg 768w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271123\">Photo courtesy of TrekBikes.com</p></div><p>It seems all the while; Trek was quietly tweaking its race machine to be faster than ever for the 2021-2022 season. The World Cup-winning geometry hasn’t changed, but the Boone gets some modern updates that will elevate ‘crossers, both amateur and professional.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike-.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Boone 2022 Black full bike\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike--297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike--800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike--120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike--768x576.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike--297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike--800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike--120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091430/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-full-bike--768x576.jpeg 768w\"></a></p><p>Unlike others that have softened their geometry to meet a gravel/cross bike all in one, Trek firmly kept the Boone as a cyclocross race bike. Pointing to the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/08/13/2020-trek-checkpoint-gravel-bike-gets-updates-wide-range-1x-drivetrain-option/\">Checkpoint as the companies gravel and wide tire drop bar offering.</a></p><h2>Trek Boone background</h2><div id=\"attachment_126646\"><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-126646\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"555\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2-120x56.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2-297x137.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2-768x355.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2-600x278.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2-120x56.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2-297x137.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2-768x355.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-2-600x278.jpg 600w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-126646\">Photo courtesy of TrekBikes.com</p></div><p>In 2013 Trek eliminated the Ion CX line and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2013/08/12/trek-introduces-crockett-the-cx-race-rocket/\">released the Crocket,</a> a new aggressive alloy cross bike. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2017/01/09/pro-bike-check-katie-comptons-national-championship-winning-trek-boone-cyclocross-bike/\">The Crocket geometry and ride showed promise, and the next move was to take the bike to carbon</a>. Released in 2013-2014, the Boone is the first ‘cross bike to incorporate a built-in suspension system — Treks ISO Speed.</p><div id=\"attachment_126645\"><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-126645\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1087\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1-120x109.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1-297x269.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1-768x696.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1-600x544.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1-120x109.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1-297x269.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1-768x696.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/TrekPartnershipSvenNys2016-1-600x544.jpg 600w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-126645\">Photo courtesy of TrekBikes.com</p></div><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2013/12/30/trek-signs-sven-nys-and-sven-vanthourenhout-for-crelan-aa-drink-team/\">In 2014 Trek partnered with Sven Nys, Sven Vanthourenhout, and AA Drink</a> for a massive move in the cyclocross world. Nys, one of the most accomplished, respected racers in the sport, helped dial the Boone to higher performance. It also skyrocketed Trek to the top of the ‘cross-cred list, now having the best in the world on their machines.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2016/04/12/trek-bicycle-sven-nys-announce-new-partnership/\">In 2016 Trek partnered doubled down on the partnership with Nys.</a> He equipped his new Sven Nys Cycling Center with Trek bikes and sponsored the long-time Ridley riding Telnet-Fidea Cycling team with Trek and Bontrager as equipment sponsors. The team put the Boone through the paces in countless muddy, sandy, frozen races worldwide, giving critical feedback to the Trek R&amp;D team.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Boone 2022 Red disc close up\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up-297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up-800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up-120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up-768x576.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up-297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up-800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up-120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091446/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-disc-close-up-768x576.jpeg 768w\"></a></p><p>The partnership has since flourished; the team, now simply Baloise-Trek, is known as one of the world’s premiere ‘cross and road development teams. They push Trek and Bontrager products to the next level in the world of mud, ruts and beyond.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors-.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors--297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors--800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors--120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors--768x576.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors--297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors--800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors--120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091426/Trek-Boone-2022-Black-race-colors--768x576.jpeg 768w\"></a></p><h2>Trek Boone — what’s new?</h2><p>For some, a ‘cross bike is a race-only machine. For others, it’s a do-it-all bike that can tackle anything. The new Boone takes a bit from both worlds, adding practical updates and race upgrades that could take you to the podium or the head of the weekend group ride.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel-297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel-800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel-120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel-768x576.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel-297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel-800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel-120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091441/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-rear-wheel-768x576.jpeg 768w\"></a></p><p><strong>Lighter and more robust</strong> — the new Trek Boone utilizes OCLV 600 Series OCLV carbon, down one tier from the top of the line OCLV 800 (think Emonda SLR) series. Trek went with OCLV 600 series for its light and forgiving nature.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot-.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Boone 2022 Red top shot\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot--297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot--800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot--120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot--768x576.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot--297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot--800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot--120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091507/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-top-shot--768x576.jpeg 768w\"></a></p><p><strong>Internal cable routing</strong> — for those that detest the nest of cables at the bars while shouldering your bike, rejoice! The new Boone eliminates the downtube cable entry point and has everything enter the headtube via headset cup. We’ve seen similar designs on Ventum and other gravel rigs, and it works well — but how will it handle power washing, and will it take on water? Only time will tell, but I’m sure Trek went through the research.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091451/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-cable-routing-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091451/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-cable-routing-.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091451/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-cable-routing-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091451/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-cable-routing--297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091451/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-cable-routing--800x600.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10091451/Trek-Boone-2022-Red-cable-routing--120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/